com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.storage

Class AdobePhotoCollection

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.storage.AdobePhoto
      • com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.storage.AdobePhotoCollection
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.internal.storage.controllers.upload.UploadDestination<AdobePhotoCollection>, java.io.Externalizable, java.io.Serializable

    public class AdobePhotoCollection
extends AdobePhoto
implements java.io.Externalizable, com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.internal.storage.controllers.upload.UploadDestination<AdobePhotoCollection>
    AdobePhotoCollection is a container of assets in a user's catalog. Each collection contains zero or more assets.

      • listAssetsOnPage

        public void listAssetsOnPage(AdobePhotoPage page,
                             AdobePhotoCollection.AdobePhotoCollectionSort sortType,
                             int limit,
                             AdobePhotoCollection.AdobePhotoCollectionFlag flag,
                             IAdobePhotoAssetsListRequestCompletionHandler completionCallback,
                             IAdobeGenericErrorCallback<com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.internal.utils.AdobeCSDKException> errorCallback)
        Lists the assets in this collection on the Adobe Photo Service asynchronously. Also populates the page with next page and previous page information.
        Parameters:
        page - the page to pass in, use null to start from the beginning.
        sortType - the sorting option.
        limit - the number of assets to return. Default value is 100, max is 500. Please note that the response may contain more than 'limit' number of assets returned if the assets at the 'limit' boundary has the same capture_date.
        flag - the result to return the assets using.
        completionCallback - gets a list of all AdobePhotoAssets for the logged in user when complete.
        errorCallback - optionally be notified of an error.
